# Part 1 - Testing Architecture

## Purpose

Testing verifies that the platform behaves correctly.

Testing protects

- Business Rules
- Domain Models
- APIs
- Events
- Workflows
- AI
- Multi-Tenancy
- Security

Testing is part of development.

Testing is never optional.

---

## Testing Philosophy

Business Requirement

↓

Architecture

↓

Implementation

↓

Testing

↓

Deployment

↓

Monitoring

Testing validates business behaviour.

It does not simply increase code coverage.

---

## Testing Pyramid

Every service follows

Unit Tests

↓

Component Tests

↓

Integration Tests

↓

Contract Tests

↓

End-to-End Tests

Higher levels execute fewer tests.

Lower levels execute more tests.

---

## Testing Ownership

Every Microservice owns

