If any answer is unclear

STOP

Review the testing architecture before implementing tests.

---

## Mandatory Rules

### MUST

- Test every business rule.
- Test every public REST API.
- Test every published and consumed event.
- Test every Flyway migration.
- Test tenant isolation.
- Test authentication and authorization.
- Test AI output validation.
- Test workflow execution.
- Use Testcontainers for infrastructure integration tests.
- Search the repository before creating new test utilities.

### MUST NOT

- Test implementation details instead of business behaviour.
- Depend on test execution order.
- Share mutable test data between tests.
- Use production databases for automated testing.
- Ignore flaky tests.
- Disable failing tests without documented approval.
- Duplicate fixtures, builders, or mocks.
- Skip security or tenant isolation tests.
- Merge code with failing automated tests.
- Treat code coverage as the only quality metric.

---

